          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "1. Deny HTTP access to /config/ directory via Apache .htaccess or server config: Deny from all. 2. Remove /config/config.inc.php from the web root entirely \u2014 config files should not be in the document root. 3. Remove .gitignore from the web root. 4. Audit all files in the document root for inadvertent information disclosure. 5. Ensure real AWS credentials are never placed in web-accessible files; use IAM instance roles or AWS Secrets Manager instead."
              }
            }
          ]
